    "Extraversion Lower levels of Extraversion were associated with better performance across reasoning tasks.",
    "Specifically, in commonsense reasoning benchmarks, models with low Extraversion significantly outperformed those with high Extraversion.",
    "This negative correlation suggests that high Extraversion may introduce distractibility, potentially impeding performance in tasks that require focused attention and analytical reasoning.",
    "Agreeableness The influence of Agreeableness on reasoning performance was minimal and inconsistent.",
    "No clear advantage was observed for models aligned with either high or low levels of Agreeableness across the benchmarks."
